{
    "Description": "<h3>Usage</h3><pre class=\"ql-syntax\" spellcheck=\"false\">component.projectRoot()\n</pre><ul><li>Returns the full directory path from where the component script is running.</li></ul><p><br></p><p>This path changes depending on the run mode:</p><ul><li><strong>Development mode</strong> / <strong>Editor</strong> - Returns a path like:</li></ul><p>\t<code>/path/to/IguanaX/config/comps/MyComponent/dev/</code></p><ul><li><strong>Commit mode</strong> (running from a deployed commit) - Returns a path like:</li></ul><p>\t<code>/path/to/IguanaX/run/MyComponent/</code></p><h3><br></h3><h3>Notes</h3><ul><li>Use this function to dynamically reference the project root directory without hardcoding paths.</li><li>Combine with Lua path utilities for robust file handling across environments.</li><li>To obtain the component’s static root folder (the directory above <code>dev/</code> that contains <code>component.json</code> and other metadata), use <code><a href=\"@component.dir\" target=\"_blank\">component.dir</a></code></li></ul><p><br></p><h3>Returns</h3><ul><li>A string with the absolute path to the current component’s project directory. <em><u>(string)</u></em></li></ul><p><br></p><h3>Example</h3><pre class=\"ql-syntax\" spellcheck=\"false\">local projectPath = component.projectRoot()\ntrace(projectPath)\n-- Output (dev mode):    \"/path/to/IguanaX/config/comps/MyComponent/dev/\"\n-- Output (commit mode): \"/path/to/IguanaX/run/MyComponent/\"\n</pre>",
    "Name": "component.projectRoot",
    "Parameters": null,
    "ParameterTable": false,
    "SummaryLine": "Returns the absolute path to the current component’s project directory."
}